parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause intermittent engine stalls, electrical shorts, and even vehicle fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle is engulfed in flames.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: A4LD Automatic Transmission Front Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seal on the A4LD automatic transmission can cause transmission fluid to leak out, leading to a loss of transmission function, and potentially causing a fire hazard due to the fluid coming into contact with the hot exhaust pipe.
symptoms: smoke coming from the exhaust pipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the A4LD automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. In extreme cases, engine failure can also cause fires, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can spread quickly, causing damage to the vehicle and potentially harming occupants. Engine fires can also lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: flames are visible in the engine compartment
smoke is visible coming from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing the engine to fail. Overheating can also cause a loss of power and acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the temperature gauge is in the red zone.
